'Joseph Francis Genet' (2 June 1914 – 1999) was a wrestler from
New Zealand.

At the 1938 British Empire Games in Sydney he won the bronze medal in the men's
62 kg category. [http://www.commonwealthgames.org.nz/Athletes/AthleteP-
rofile.aspx?Print=&ContactID=26707&id=1 Profile at the New Zealand Olympic
Committee]
